		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You're probably gonna have to revamp the shop menu anyway, since it's <sup>close to</sup> full-up now (once you add more abilities). Probably break into sub-menus.<br /><br />An addition that currently might make sense: eat-in (that is, immediately applied) <s>riceballs*</s> pizza. Even if you do normally refill health between stages, an eat-in XL would make sense [starting with 8 rather than 4]. Of course, a small discount would apply compared to take-out.<br /><br /><strong>Bug report:</strong> You can reorganize the pause menu on page 2 with select, but it doesn't move the actual actions (at least, not Exit Level- I moved it to the bottom, and it did nothing there, but empty slot 1 then would still exit level). It also doesn't save the new positions…unsurprising as I don't think this was quite intended.<br /><br />hey, the shop menu doesn't wrap horizontally. That would reduce the maximum number of presses to get to any item by 3, y'know.<br /><br />A buy-multiple (10?) option would be nice?<br /><br />The shop doesn't tell you &quot;you can't have more of those&quot; when you try to buy more than 99 of an item, though at least it doesn't charge you.<br /><br /><strong>Bug report:</strong> fireballs can stick in ground. Bounce a normal shot from an exactly four-block-high drop [there's one in last room of 1-1…but no fire enemy] and it'll stick into the lower ground. (Five doesn't work.)<br /><br />Huh, world1's music is gone. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />*<span style="font-size: 75%; line-height: normal">Eat your hamburgers, Apollo.</span>

		

