	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">qalle wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">if you slow down just before falling off a block and turn back while falling, you &quot;zip&quot; back up. I created an animated GIF.</div><br />This is the sort of helpful collision bug that often pops up in Nova's games and eventually gets turned into a similar official behavior.<br /><br />Something similar happened when I <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=10144" class="postlink">remade Nova's <em>Forehead Block Guy</em> in Pygame</a>. The original had a bug allowing sticking to a wall and jumping from it, and I recast it as the ability to grab a ledge and scoot up like in <em>Prince of Persia</em> or <em>Super Smash Bros.</em> My version added a tradeoff between mobility and offense: ledge grabbing can't be used while tossing blocks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


